<plot>"Home" in times of globalization Ze ozzer vun is form Karlsruh'. Zere is his home. Zat's why he speaks a little bit strrhange. Zen he goes somevere else and novun understands him... In three minutes the filmmaker explains in his hometowns dialect, what "home" is about. He takes us on a trip from southern to northern Germany, ending up in the middle of nowhere in Brazil. In a humouristic and, at the same time, philosophic way, the film combines Foto-film, animation and real sequences. The english subtitles translate not only the words but also the dialect spoken. A small dialect-roadmovie.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?137224</url></doc>
